      },
      {
        label: "House rules",
        pills: [{ t: "Weis only with a trick" }, { t: "Sack (min. 21)" }, { t: "Real cutting", on: true }],
      },
    ],
    legend: [
      "<strong>Quick start:</strong> one click — private table, all empty seats taken by the chosen AI.",
      "<strong>Variant:</strong> Kreuz (teams), Solo (everyone for themselves) or Bodensee (two players) — see chapter 9.",
      "<strong>Joining:</strong> Open = anyone sits down · On request = you confirm each join · Invite only = the table is visible to invitees only.",
      "<strong>AI strength</strong> for auto-filled seats: solid heuristic, the trained neural network, or random for practice.",
      "<strong>Auto-fill:</strong> if a seat stays empty, the AI takes over after a short wait — nobody waits forever.",
      "<strong>Point target:</strong> how far it accumulates (suggested: Kreuz 1000, Solo/Bodensee 500).",
      "<strong>Follow-up game:</strong> classically the winner deals — or it is dealt out and whoever holds the WELI begins.",
      "<strong>Announcement ladder:</strong> from “trump only” to “everything” incl. Gumpf (chapter 7).",
      "<strong>House rules:</strong> Weis only with a trick and the Sack rule (chapter 8), plus real cutting: before the deal, the person to the dealer’s right actually cuts — or knocks.",
    ],
    s11H2: "What else the platform can do",
    features: [
      { icon: "🪑", title: "Lobby & tables", text: "Open tables, join (open, on request or invite only) — the AI fills free seats on request." },
      { icon: "🤖", title: "AI players", text: "Three strengths: random (for practice), a solid heuristic, and a trained neural network as the strongest opponent." },
      { icon: "💬", title: "Chats", text: "Lobby chat for everyone, table chat from the waiting phase (lives on into the game), and private conversations." },
      { icon: "✉️", title: "Direct messages", text: "Click a name → direct message. You decide who may write you: everyone or friends only; individuals can be blocked." },
      { icon: "🤝", title: "Friends", text: "Request, accept, unfriend — and on birthdays the lobby reminds you to send congratulations." },
      { icon: "🟢", title: "Presence & pause", text: "Four states on the name dot: green online, blue at a table, orange away (AFK button), grey offline with “last seen”." },
      { icon: "🎬", title: "Replays", text: "Every game can be replayed move by move — including Weis announcements. Shareable publicly via link on request." },
      { icon: "📊", title: "Stats & leaderboard", text: "Games, wins, rates per variant in your profile; the public leaderboard is strictly opt-in." },
      { icon: "🛡️", title: "Privacy", text: "Every profile field individually visible to: everyone, logged-in users, friends or nobody. Also for online status and stats." },
      { icon: "🚨", title: "Reporting & moderation", text: "Report abusive behavior right at the name; admins review every case. Plus a word filter in chat." },
      { icon: "🔔", title: "Miss nothing", text: "Browser push for join requests, a hint on new messages, re-entry after a connection drop." },
      { icon: "🌗", title: "Comfort", text: "German & English, light, dark and high-contrast themes, installable as an app (PWA)." },
    ],
    outroHtml:
      "<strong>Ready for your first trick?</strong> The fastest way to learn is in the game — the AI has infinite patience.",
    outroCta: "Play now",
